## Writing for onboarding

Use the [onboarding guidance](https://spectrum.adobe.com/page/writing-for-onboarding/) when planning education and adoption flows.

- **Plan intentionally** ‚Äì reflect what users already know, clarify why they are there, sequence topics logically, keep tutorials focused on a single tool or technique, limit flows to roughly ten steps, and set expectations (outcome, timing, prerequisites) up front.
- **Communicate supportively** ‚Äì use lightweight, encouraging language; introduce jargon only with definitions; avoid pointing directly at UI chrome unless essential; personalize when possible; and prefer in-product learning experiences over forcing users into a browser.
- **Choose the right pattern** ‚Äì Spectrum highlights banners, cards, coach marks, empty states, modals, tooltips, tours, triggered elements, tutorials, and video demos. Select the pattern that matches the information density and desired level of interruption, and explain why users should engage with it.
